{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UdQZ75iq72o8D2NSpMKJpo","type":"tool_result","content":"# ray/upgrade_version\n# Upgrade ray-head and ray-worker deployments from rayproject/ray:2.8.0 to 2.9.0\n\nprompt: |\n  A Ray cluster is running with an older Ray image ({{params.from_image}}).\n\n  Your task: upgrade both ray-head and ray-worker deployments to\n  {{params.to_image}}.\n\n  Requirements:\n  - Update the image in both deployments.\n  - Ensure rollouts complete successfully.\n\n  Suggested commands:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-head ray-head={{params.to_image}}\n  kubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-worker ray-worker={{params.to_image}}\n  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=120s\n  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=120s\n  ```\n\n  Success criteria: both deployments use {{params.to_image}} and remain ready.\n\nparams:\n  from_image:\n    default: rayproject/ray:2.8.0\n    description: Current Ray image the cluster is running before the upgrade\n  to_image:\n    default: rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n    description: Target Ray image to upgrade both deployments to\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 360\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n        sleep: 0\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod ray-client >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-client.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/ray-client --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/upgrade_version/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 180","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9820c1ac-01b8-4f2d-8f2f-0fc2fdfde19b","uuid":"7f7bd9fc-efed-49bb-a61d-d9be603d9395","timestamp":"2026-06-24T06:37:21.409Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# ray/upgrade_version\n# Upgrade ray-head and ray-worker deployments from rayproject/ray:2.8.0 to 2.9.0\n\nprompt: |\n  A Ray cluster is running with an older Ray image ({{params.from_image}}).\n\n  Your task: upgrade both ray-head and ray-worker deployments to\n  {{params.to_image}}.\n\n  Requirements:\n  - Update the image in both deployments.\n  - Ensure rollouts complete successfully.\n\n  Suggested commands:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-head ray-head={{params.to_image}}\n  kubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-worker ray-worker={{params.to_image}}\n  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=120s\n  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=120s\n  ```\n\n  Success criteria: both deployments use {{params.to_image}} and remain ready.\n\nparams:\n  from_image:\n    default: rayproject/ray:2.8.0\n    description: Current Ray image the cluster is run